gomodel:SYNGO_2796  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.1: \"Distribution of Wnt signaling proteins in the mouse hippocampus\"\n- \"Puncta of Wnt3a and Frizzled-4 signals showed extensive co-localizations with PSD-95 (Fig. 1, b-d and f-h), indicating their localization at the synaptic regions. As Frizzled-4 physically interacts with PSD-95 (39), this Wnt receptor is most likely localized on the post-synaptic membrane. Dishevelled-3 puncta overlapped with PSD-95 to a lesser extent (Fig. 1, j-l), whereas β-catenin displayed a more diffused pattern with signal clusters (Fig. 1, n-p), which is consistent with previous studies (40). These results suggest that Wnt signaling operates at hippocampal synapses.\". Experimental description: - \"Hippocampal slices (400 μm) were prepared from 3-4-week mice...\"\n- Species of recombinant Wnt3a used in Fig.5 is not stated in the paper." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2018-03-07" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2796" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

